    TypedDefRefs

    The TypedDefRef class represents an AUTOSAR definition reference with the type of the AUTOSAR (MDF) model. So every TypedDefRef knows which Definition, Configuration and Value element is correct for the Definition path. The DEF_TYPE, CONFIG_TYPE and VALUE_TYPE are Java generics and are used many APIs to return the specific type of a request. In addition the most TypedDefRefs also provide additional TypedDefRef.TypeInfo data, like the Multiplicity of the element. See TypedDefRef.TypeInfo javadoc for more details.

    DefRefs are constant; their values cannot be changed after they are created. This class is immutable!

    • Method Detail

      • asDefinitionOf

        @PublishedMethod
public CONFIG_TYPE asDefinitionOf(MIObject modelObject)
        Checks if this object is the definition of the passed modelObject and an instance of modelObjectClass. If the check is true, the method returns the object casted to modelObjectClass. Otherwise the method return null.

        Note: This method tests also refinements. So, if the modelObject is refined of this definition, it will also yield to true.

        Note: This method is an implicit null and classToCheck class check. This means, if it returns true, the modelObject is an instance of classToCheck.

        The method will return false, if the passed modelObject is removed. The method will return false, if the passed modelObject is invisible.

        Parameters:
        modelObject - The modelObject to check.
        Returns:
        object, if this is the definition of the modelObject and it is instance of modelObjectClass. Otherwise null.
        See Also:
        isDefinitionOf(MIObject)

      • getDefinitionObject

        @PublishedMethod
public DEF_TYPE getDefinitionObject(IProjectContext projectContext)
        Returns the MDF definition object.

        Returns the AUTOSAR definition object if the DefRef has a wildcard. If the passed DefRef is a wildcard DefRef, but has no AUTOSAR definition, the method tries to find one Vendor definition. If one Vendor definition exists, the definition is returned. If none or more then one Definition exist null is returned , see DefRef.getPossibleDefinitionsForDefRefWithWildcard(IProjectContext) for more details.

        Returns null, if no definition exists.
        Overrides:
        getDefinitionObject in class DefRef
        Returns:
        The MDF definition object, or null if no definition object exists.

      • getPossibleDefinitionsForDefRefWithWildcard

        @PublishedMethod
public java.util.List<DEF_TYPE> getPossibleDefinitionsForDefRefWithWildcard(IProjectContext projectContext)
        Gets the possible definitions of the DefRef.

        Attention: This methods returns the AUTOSAR standard definition object, before it returns any other definition. If the passed DefRef is a wildcard DefRef, but has no AUTOSAR definition, the method tries to find any Vendor definition and will return the list of vendor definitions. If the DefRef has an AUTOSAR definition the method will return a list with only the AUTOSAR definition!

        This DefRef object should have wildcards, otherwise this method makes no sense and returns the definition form DefRef.getDefinitionObject(IProjectContext).

        Overrides:
        getPossibleDefinitionsForDefRefWithWildcard in class DefRef
        Parameters:
        projectContext - the project context
        Returns:
        the possible definitions for the DefRef
